<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Curator</title>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all' %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'application' %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <header class="center">
      <h1 class="header-title">Curator</h1>
      <h3 class="header-subtitle">News Analyzed</h3>
        <%= form_tag("/search", method: "get") do %>
          <%= text_field_tag :term, nil, class: 'search-field' %>
          <%= submit_tag("Search", :class => 'right waves-effect waves-light btn-large') %>
        <% end %>
    </header>
    <div class='yielded-index'>
      <%= yield %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer class="page-footer cyan lighten-1">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col l6 s12">
          <p class="grey-text text-lighten-4 footer-text">Curator uses the Reddit API and the NYTimes API to pull text data when queried with a search term. Curator has a Rails backend and sends data to the JavaScript and jQuery frontend, which shows up on a beautiful single-page app that was built using Materialize.</p>
          <p class="grey-text text-lighten-4 footer-text">Curator is built to support API calls. If you'd like to use it, <a class="amber-text text-lighten-4" href="https://github.com/JoshJHWu/Curator-a-">check out our documentation.</a></p>
          <p class="grey-text text-lighten-4 footer-text">Curator was our product for <a class="amber-text text-lighten-4" href="http://angelhack.com/portfolio-item/brooklyn-usa-may-7-8-2016/">AngelHack Brooklyn 2016</a>. We built it in 1.5 days!</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col l5 offset-l1 s12">
          <h5 class="white-text">Who we are</h5>
          <ul>
            <li class="footer-text grey-text text-lighten-4"><a class="amber-text text-lighten-4" href="https://github.com/JoshJHWu">Josh Wu</a></li>
            <li class="footer-text grey-text text-lighten-4"><a class="amber-text text-lighten-4" href="https://github.com/mindplace">Esther Leytush</a> put together custom Reddit API calls with recursive comment grabbing.</li>
            <li class="footer-text grey-text text-lighten-4"><a class="amber-text text-lighten-4" href="https://github.com/seodo">John Seo</a></li>
            <li class="footer-text grey-text text-lighten-4"><a class="amber-text text-lighten-4" href="https://github.com/RebeccaKleinberg">Rebecca Kleinberg</a> </li>
            <li class="footer-text grey-text text-lighten-4"><a class="amber-text text-lighten-4" href="https://github.com/sonomar">Lawson Marlowe</a> designed and coded the frontend JavaScript, jQuery, and AJAX, as well as managed layout and styling.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-copyright">
      <div class="container footer-text">
      Â© 2016 Josh Wu, Esther Leytush, John Seo, Rebecca Kleinberg, Lawson Marlowe
      <a class="amber-text text-lighten-4 right footer-text" href="https://github.com/JoshJHWu/Curator-a-">Come see our code on Github</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
